{%- comment -%}
  Gift wrap (spec §7: "gift-wrap checkbox (+$5)"). Explicitly a placeholder —
  same precedent as wishlist/compare in Milestone 3: a real, fully wired
  toggle with no backend behind it yet, since actually adding a gift-wrap
  line item requires a specific gift-wrap product variant that only exists
  once a merchant creates one (a generic theme can't assume its id). Reuses
  switch.liquid exactly as spec names it ("Switch — used for... gift wrap"),
  not a bespoke checkbox.

  Wiring this up for real, once a merchant has a gift-wrap product, is a
  one-line change: assets/cart-utils.js's addToCart already exists (built in
  Milestone 7) and this switch's `change` event is the only thing that would
  need a listener added.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if settings.cart_show_gift_wrap -%}
  <div class="cart-gift-wrap">
    {% render 'switch', id: 'CartGiftWrap', name: 'gift_wrap', label: 'cart.gift_wrap' | t %}
  </div>
{%- endif -%}
